# Project Rules

## First-Time Setup

This project uses the **detritus MCP server** for knowledge base access. If the `kb_get`, `kb_list`, `kb_search` tools are not available, run the `/setup-detritus` workflow to install it.

## Foundational Principles

Fetch kb_get(name="meta/truthseeker") at conversation start when the detritus MCP server is available. Core mandate: push back with evidence, question assumptions, prove before acting, radical honesty even when uncomfortable. Never ask permission to challenge — if something appears wrong or unproven, say so directly.

## Knowledge Base

General knowledge (ooo ecosystem, testing, Go patterns) is served by the **detritus MCP server**. The MCP tools `kb_get`, `kb_list`, and `kb_search` are auto-invoked based on keywords in prompts.

## Workflows

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `/setup-detritus` | Install or update detritus MCP server |
| `/truthseeker` | Foundational principles - ALWAYS ACTIVE, do not invoke |
| `/plan` | Requirements analysis (delegates to MCP) |
| `/plan-export` | Generate planning documents with diagrams and export to PDF |
| `/diagrams` | Mermaid diagram reference - syntax, types, and when to use each |
| `/create` | Scaffold a new app - backend, full-stack, or desktop (delegates to MCP) |
| `/grow` | Learn from conversation corrections - distill fixes into KB updates |
| `/optimize` | Re-index and optimize KB docs for agent retrieval efficiency |
| `/line-of-sight` | Line-of-sight code style - flat code, early returns |
| `/research-first` | Exhaust available resources before asking the user |
